The 31-year-old woman&#8217;s body was discovered at a communal toilet on Monday. CAPE TOWN - A man has been arrested in connection with the murder of a woman in Khayelitsha.Her body was discovered at communal toilet on Monday.The police s Frederick van Wyk says the 31-year-old woman s body was found in RR block in Khayelitsha. It is believed the deceased was murdered at a residence in Khayelitsha and the body was later moved to the public toilets. A 27-year old suspect who was arrested on Tuesday is expected to appear in the Khayelitsha Magistrates Court on Thursday.The circumstances resemble the murder of Sinixolo Mafevuka, whose body was also found at communal toilets in the same informal settlement in March.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)